HEADWORD: demodulator
<hw>demodulator</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Electronics)</fld> <def>An
electronic device which extracts the modulation from a radio carrier
wave, and outputs the original information-bearing signal.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> detector.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]⟦br⟧
